# ══════════════════════════════════════
#  SECRETS — never commit these
# ══════════════════════════════════════
# SSH private keys for the Nexia droplet. These should live OUTSIDE the repo
# entirely — this entry is a safety net, not a substitute for moving them.
Key Backups/
*.pem
*.ppk
id_rsa*
id_ed25519*
known_hosts*

# Environment / credentials
.env
.env.*
*.key

# The Nexia auth/lesson server is NOT published. It stays local — the client
# talks to it over the API described in API_CONTRACT.md, and that contract is
# the only part that's public.
nexia-server/
*.bak-*

# ══════════════════════════════════════
#  DEPENDENCIES & BUILD OUTPUT
# ══════════════════════════════════════
node_modules/
dist/
out/
*.vsix

# Compiled installer — 157 MB, well over GitHub's 100 MB hard limit.
# Ship it through GitHub Releases instead of committing it.
NexiaSetup*.exe
setup_base.exe
packer.exe

# TypeScript incremental build cache
*.tsbuildinfo

# Bundled SDK (generated by pack-sdk.bat — too large for git)
sdk/bin/
sdk/include/
sdk/lib/
!sdk/.gitkeep

# Installer build intermediates
installer/*.exe
installer/*.o
installer/*.obj
*.res.o

# ══════════════════════════════════════
#  INTERNAL NOTES (kept locally, not published)
# ══════════════════════════════════════
# Session-by-session dev journal. Useful to keep, but it's internal context
# rather than documentation, and it goes stale fast.
notes.md

# Design spec for the private auth/lesson server. The server isn't published and
# isn't meant to be reimplemented, so this is internal design context, not docs.
API_CONTRACT.md

# ══════════════════════════════════════
#  LOCAL / EDITOR CRUFT
# ══════════════════════════════════════
.claude/
*.lnk
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
.DS_Store
.vs/
.vscode/
*.user
*.suo

# Generated from package.json by scripts/gen-version.js
installer/version_generated.h
